view the conservatives at election time – possibly as early as fallthe key thing is getting the money out the door and getting the work done says liberal consultant bob richardson a friend of bairds for  years thats what canadians want to know did he get it done if the answers yes then great if no youve got big problems for the governmenta fall election likely would be too soon for any comprehensive review of the spending plan but not too soon for communities across the country to have a good sense of how well the money is flowing if torontos any indication things may not go well baird recently rejected the citys proposal to pump stimulus funds into new streetcars because their completion date fell outside the programs early  deadline his frustration with mayor david miller led to the infamous epithet and it must be noted a hasty and full apologyjohn is playing a critical role for the government says richardson of course finance minister jim flahertys a heavyweight but bairds the guy with his hand on the infrastructure spigot thats a top issue – if not the top issue across the country richardson addshows that for pressure on john russell baird rusty to his palsprobably nothing too overwhelming at  hes the former boy wonder who quickly morphed into prime minister stephen harpers mr fixit after the conservatives won their first minority in early  harper named baird to the presidency of the frontline treasury board then parachuted him into the environment portfolio to relieve a faltering rona ambrose aka harpers pit bull he took on new liberal leader stéphane dion when dion was seen as the green saviour of canadian politics hows he done it ability energy intelligence and a solid work ethic sure but hes also close to the boss arguably baird is harpers cabinet favourite a leader seen as prickly and aloof is described by baird as sharing a strong relationship with him we have great discussions we debate ideas all the timefriends and colleagues applaud sharp political skills for his rocket ride in federal politicsjohn baird was one of the people who supported stephen harper before a lot of other people figured it out says jaime watt a conservative political strategist and another longtime baird friend baird cochaired harpers  bid for the new conservative partys leadership and that same year played a similar role in the federal election in which the liberals won a minorityi liked harper i believed in a new conservative party i thought it was unhealthy for canada not to have a real opposition and i got behind him very early in the province says baird then he took a risk by  hed been a prominent mpp and cabinet minister from the ottawaarea riding of nepeancarleton for  years a safe and comfy seat nevertheless he resigned and ran federally in the much more volatile ottawa westnepean riding john has extraordinary political instincts says ontario progressive conservative leader tim hudak when he made the leap to federal politics many more cautious people recommended he stay put at queens park they didnt see stephen harper emerging as anything special on the national level other mpps whod been headhunted by the conservatives thought the liberals would be in power in ottawa for a very long timea gutsy move no question but it was no secret baird also a favourite of former premier mike harris the guys got a knack didnt get along with new leader ernie eves it was personal say colleagues and went beyond evess annoyance over bairds early support for flaherty in the leadership race moreover by  the conservatives were out of power in queens parktheres more with harper the pm values loyalty and baird is the dictionary definition of the word of his early support for harpers leadership baird says i wasnt a member of caucus trying to position myself for the future and so there was a lot of trust in our relationship from the beginninghe knows im loyalpolitics is brutal a royal court of intrigue colleagues wait in the wings sniffing for that first whiff of blood not baird nobody interviewed sees him as a schemer only canadian chamber of commerce president perrin beatty who hired student baird political science queens when he was communications minister cautioned one shouldnt rule that out as a possibility at some time in his career  but hes not consumed with the desire to be prime ministerbaird is blunt i dont have any plans i think some people probably think about that i dontsources say harper doesnt see baird as a threat if baird ever were to think about running it would be on harpers timetable and with his counsel and blessingbaird should be able to count on laureen harper described as funny charming and a bon vivant by friends he often escorts the pms wife to events in the capitalmrs harper is fantastic says baird we get along finetall husky and looking fit baird sat down with the toronto star on a muggy toronto afternoon at an outdoor café he lived near queens park for a decade loves the city and waves often to passersby who spot the familiar dudley doright jutting jaw hes not into sports oh god no says watt loves fast food and his weight goes up and down like a seesaw hes recently dropped pounds by eschewing carbs he doesnt so much laugh as cackle and hes funny if not always intentionally so since he was  his big passion in life was to be an mpp at queens park trulywhy he doesnt really know his dads favourite uncle russell boucher was an ottawaarea mp in the s but thats not it i just thought that would be a really cool thingsays richardson thats off the nerd meterbaird was born and raised in nepean his parents gerald and marianne divorced when he was  he has one sister and lived alternately with each parentat  and in grade  french immersion at d aubrey moodie school in nepean kay stanley was his english teacher he worked on her unsuccessful  campaign for the conservative nomination in nepeancarleton later getting to know her sister marjory lebreton powerhouse in the mulroney government and now in the senatestanley once told the class shed been talking with joe clark oh my god baird thought i cant believe she can talk to joe clarkanother cacklehes single lives in a nepean townhouse characterized by richardson as a permanent bachelor pad with his grey tabby thatcher whats the cat like exactly like mrs thatcher says richardson of the former frosty british pmone of the things thats special about john is how he treats his friends says watt you know when you are friends with a politician youre going to have to do the bulk of the work but hes different he shares the heavy lifting  he knows how to nurture friendshipsfriends bristle when hes described as a loudmouthed hothead too often just screaming his head off in the house of commons looking wild as one political observer puts it but opponents dont always grasp that his tongue is supposed to be in cheek baird cites ndp leader jack layton as proof he works well across the political spectrum layton isnt so sure he called olivia and me a twoheaded monster responds layton referring to his wife new democrat mp olivia chow maybe it was in jest but it felt pretty personalchow who represents trinityspadina may turn out to be bairds nemesis in his recent challenge she doesnt buy the argument toronto should have been able to match other cities in getting the spending criteria right from the beginning in a democratic society it should be up to the municipality to decide how it wants to spend the money she says chow is helping to organize a public protest against baird later this summer and asks people to come and put screws into giant letters spelling screwed at a kensington market site she hopes it will be a lasting image for canadians before parliament resumessays chow lets show john baird toronto wont be screwed withread more about stephen harper john bairddelivered dailythe morning headlines newslettersubscribethe toronto star and thestarcom each property of toronto star newspapers limited one yonge street th floor toronto on me e y